        "position": 5,
        "title": "It's a nice general dog shirt, but didn't do anything for her anxiety",
        "text": "As a general dog outfit, this is nice - it's soft and cute, and the colour really stands out. The material has a decent stretch to it, and it was easy to wash, and the colour didn't fade. I like the velcro, it isn't the typical course or rough material, although when my dog was trying it out, it got stuck to her plush doghouse, which ended up following her around all day.As an anxiety vest, I don't know if it does anything special. I call it her \"hug shirt,\" as it feels like it just gives her a nice snug hug, although it doesn't seem to help her anxiety or personality. To her, it's just a normal shirt, which does feel warm when she wears it. Nothing bad, yet nothing special.",
