      {
        "position": 6,
        "title": "Stretchable Dog Anxiety Vest that Calms Our Dog",
        "text": "I have one dog that lives with severe anxiety when it comes to rain, thunder, and snow storms. He also experiences anxiety with loud noises like fireworks. So, anything natural to help ease his anxiety I jump for and will try. The first thing I like about this anxiety vest is the material and the wide Velcro closures. The material is smooth, soft, stretchable, and breathable. The vest appears and feels of good quality material and we got dark purple and the color is solid and consistent.I love that the vest is machine washable and can be dried in the clothing dryer. However, as not to breakdown the Velcro closures (and causing curling up of the Velcro), I may just hang dry the vest. The vest is not water resistant which means it may get urine on it depending on the location of the bottom of the vestWhen I put the vest on my dog that has anxiety, he was calm and actually sat and laid down. I think the vest is a hit for him based of how he settled down when he got into the vest. Also, it was easy to put the vest on him and to take it off of him.We measured our dog’s chest before ordering the vest to try and get him the best size for him. He measured out to fit a small and the vest fits fine. With the Velcro closures and the vest being stretchable I was able to make the vest fit snug like a hug or to loosen it if necessary. Due to the dog’s comfortability I feel comfortable letting him sleep in the vest overnight if needed.I even tried it on my slightly bigger sized elderly dog and it fit and he didn’t resist getting into the vest. He was calm and seemed ok wearing the vest. It was easy to get him into and out of the vest even with him having a thicker and fluffier coat and his fur didn’t get caught into the Velcro.The price of the vest is reasonable for the quality of the vest and its effect on my dog’s anxiety. The vest material is a lightweight, and a cotton blend, that is strong and stretchable and I think that it can hold up to much usage and many washes. Overall, we like the vest and would consider getting a second one for our elderly dog.",
